Two people were critically injured in a multi-vehicle crash involving a truck on the N3 north in Germiston, Ekurhuleni, on Saturday morning, paramedics said.
ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene at about 7.30am and found a woman, believed to be in her 30s, trapped in her car. Fire and rescue personnel later extracted her from the car, ER24 spokeswoman Annine Siddall said.
She was airlifted by the ER24 and One Plan Medical helicopter to a nearby hospital for further medical care.
A man believed to be in his 40s, was found lying next to the truck and was treated and transported to hospital for further care. The circumstances surrounding the accident were not yet known, Siddall said.